GhostParse-Experimental

⚠️ EXPERIMENTAL C PARSER PROJECT

GhostParse is an experimental C-based parsing project created for systems programming practice, file/data handling research, and controlled lab experimentation.

This repository is early-stage and should not be considered production-ready.

⸻

Overview

GhostParse was created to explore how C programs can read, process, and interpret structured input data.

The project demonstrates:

* C programming
* Input parsing
* File handling
* Basic program structure
* Debugging and testing workflow
* Experimental systems development

⸻

Repository Contents

* GhostParse.c — main C source file
* GhostParse.exe — compiled Windows executable
* IDE/project configuration files

⸻

Build Instructions

Compile with GCC:

gcc GhostParse.c -o GhostParse

On Windows with MinGW:

gcc GhostParse.c -o GhostParse.exe

⸻

Example Usage

./GhostParse

or on Windows:

.\GhostParse.exe

⸻

Skills Demonstrated

* C programming
* Systems-level development
* Manual compilation
* Input processing
* Debugging
* Technical experimentation

⸻

Status

Experimental / early-stage.

Future improvements may include:

* Cleaner input validation
* Better error handling
* More detailed documentation
* Test files
* Example output
* Cross-platform build notes

⸻

